Business Brief -- R.G. Barry Corp.:
   `Strong' 4th-Period Results
   Expected at Shoe Concern
Separately, R.G. Barry expanded its board to 10 members
from nine. The new board member, Christian Galvis, 49 years
old, is the company's executive vice president of operations.
   The news comes on the heels of yesterday's announcement
that the company's president, chief executive officer and
director, Wade Harn, 50, will leave the company. Mr. Harn's
responsibilities will be absorbed by R.G. Barry Chairman
Gordon Zacks, 58. Charles Ostrander, 44, executive vice
president of operations, will succeed Mr. Harn on the board.